black mechanical computer keyboard with function keys
data.utilizationMethod: Use one of the larger keys (e.g., the space-bar or Enter key) as the press surface. Rest your index finger on that key and push straight down until the key bottoms out. The key’s built-in switch and return spring give a clear travel distance, progressive resistance, an audible click, and automatic rebound—closely mimicking the feel of depressing and releasing the virtual red button.
